It is used to find out number of lines, word count, byte and characters count in the files specified in the file.

$ wc FILE_NAME
$ wc FILE_NAME FILE_NAME
$ wc -l FILE_NAME			        (prints the number of lines)
$ wc -l FILE_NAME FILE_NAME
$ wc -w FILE_NAME			        (prints the number of words)
$ wc -w FILE_NAME FILE_NAME
$ wc -c FILE_NAME			        (print the byte counts)
$ wc -c FILE_NAME FILE_NAME
$ wc -m FILE_NAME			        (print the character counts)
$ wc -m FILE_NAME FILE_NAME   
$ wc -L FILE_NAME 			        (print the length of longest line)
$ wc -L FILE_NAME FILE_NAME
